./

aa_dagjk.pro


The purpose of aa_dagjk is to estimate errors on stacked quantity using a modified delete-a-group jknife technique, a statistical estimate of the standard deviation that incorporates both the variance of the estimator and its bias.

See Eq.1 Kott, 2001.

When employed using random rejection, there are no theoretical advantages to DAGJK over the traditional ‘leave one out’ jackknife method. The main motivation for its use is that the grouping of data allows for significant gains in computational efficiency when applied to large samples while maintaining precision in the (nearly) unbiased confidence interval of the population parameter.

This method ranks each spectra by a selected property (randomly, NUV-r, stellar mass), it then calculates the gas fraction iteratively, while discarding, in turn, a separate random subset of galaxies from the sample.

e.g. for 100 galaxies in original stack and 20% resampling, aa_dagjk will remove 0-19,20-39,40-59,60-79, 80-100

The resulting distribution of the stacked flux/mass/gas fractions is saved in the .sav structure.\

Examples

aa_dagjk is a main level procedure included in aa_dagjk.pro:

IDL> aa_dagjk, 'path/to/aa_measure_output', 'path/to/file.cfg'
Iteratively stacks galaxies indexed by aa_stack, discarding 20% per iteration. Reduction and spectral measurements are automatic.

top source aa_dagjk

Error analysis, ALFALFA software

aa_dagjk, stackingdir, cfgfile

Procedure

1. Restore stacked structure.

2. Rank galaxies by NUV-r, mu_star, M_star, C-index or Random (default NUV-r), and select 20% of the targets.

3. Stack following 'aa_stack.pro'.

4. Save a structure for each of the stacking repetition.

5. Measure the signal in the stacked spectrum, using the reduction parameters from 'aa_measure.pro'

6. Update and modify the corresponding stack field with the values measured. Which quantity is stacked, and if a correction for confusion has to be applied is read from the structure (set during 'aa_stack.pro').

Outputs

'output/output_bin_no.sav' - Modified structure containing the stack, now with DAG jackknife fluxes/HI masses/gas fractions

jknife_flx,jknife_mhi,jknife_gf - 5 independent Jacknife measures of stacked flux, HI mass or gas fraction.

Parameters

stackingdir in required type=string

of the output directory of aa_measure.pro

cfgfile in required type=string

Configuration file containing path to sample catalogue, options for stacking routine, bin edges (see 'inputexample.cfg').

Other attributes

Uses:

f_bmask, b_fit, progbar, freqshift

Bugs:

It is possible for aa_dagjk program can handle multiple stacking directories, however to enable this functionality the following lines:

pro aa_dagjk, stackingdir folders = [stackingdir]
must be replaced with:
pro aa_dagjk, dir1, dir2, ..., dirN folders = [dir1, dir2, ..., dirN]
